claims:
1. A method of training a policy network to search relational paths in a knowledge graph, the method comprising:
identifying, using a reasoning module, a plurality of first outgoing links from a current node in the knowledge graph;
masking, using the reasoning module, one or more links from the plurality of first outgoing links to form a plurality of second outgoing links;
traversing the knowledge graph using the plurality of second outgoing links;
rewarding the reasoning module with a reward of one when a node corresponding to an observed answer is reached; and
rewarding the reasoning module with a reward identified by a reward shaping network when a node not corresponding to the observed answer is reached.

9. A system for training a policy network to search relational paths in a knowledge graph, the system comprising:
a memory;
a processor coupled to the memory and configured to;
identify a plurality of first outgoing links from a current node in the knowledge graph;
mask one or more links from the plurality of first outgoing links to form a plurality of second outgoing links;
traverse the knowledge graph using the plurality of second outgoing links;
reward the reasoning module with a reward of one when a node corresponding to an observed answer is reached; and
reward a reasoning module with a reward identified by a reward shaping network when a node not corresponding to the observed answer is reached.

17. A non-transitory machine-readable medium having stored thereon machine-readable instructions executable to cause a machine to perform operations that of trains a policy network to search relational paths in an incomplete knowledge graph, the operations comprising:
receiving a query;
identifying, using a reasoning module, a plurality of first outgoing links from a starting node in the knowledge graph;
masking, using the reasoning module, one or more links from the plurality of first outgoing links to form a plurality of second outgoing links; and
traversing the incomplete knowledge graph using the plurality of second outgoing links until an observed answer is identified or is not found.
